<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[182,1073,156,740]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Remarks: This species was put into synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="(ANTON, 1838)" baseAuthorityName="ANTON" baseAuthorityYear="1838" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="semicostatum" subGenus="Pusia">
<emphasis box="[817,914,566,590]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Vexillum</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[931,993,566,590]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Pusia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">semicostatum</emphasis>
(ANTON, 1838)
</taxonomicName>
by different authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Pechar, P. &amp; Prior, C. &amp; Parkinson, B." box="[702,905,604,628]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref12377" refString="Pechar, P., Prior, C. &amp; Parkinson, B. (1980): Mitre shells from the Pacific and Indian Oceans. - 126 pp., 56 plates, Bathurst N. S. W." type="book" year="1980">Pechar &amp; al. 1980</bibRefCitation>
– plate 54, fig. 4; 
<bibRefCitation author="Springsteen, F. J. &amp; Leobrera, F. M." box="[214,554,641,665]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref12761" refString="Springsteen, F. J. &amp; Leobrera, F. M. (1986): Shells of the Philippines. - 377 pp., 100 plates, Manila." type="book" year="1986">Springsteen &amp; Leobrera 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Okutani, T." box="[572,728,641,665]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref12357" refString="Okutani, T. (2000): Marine Mollusks in Japan. - 1173 pp., Tokyo." type="book" year="2000">Okutani 2000</bibRefCitation>
; Turner 2001), but is easy to distinguish from the latter species by the red-orange colour and the regular white dots only in the anterior part of the whorls.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
